08/04/2010
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- The EU and the United States will continue to assist Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) in its Euro-Atlantic bid, US Deputy Secretary of State James Steinberg and Spanish Foreign Minister Miguel Angel Moratinos said in Sarajevo Wednesday (April 7th) as they completed their visit. Moratinos, whose country holds the rotating EU presidency, voiced hope that the bloc will add BiH to its visa-free regime in June. Steinberg next travelled to Belgrade for talks with Serbian officials. His Balkan tour ends with a visit to Kosovo. (RTRS, Srna, Fena, BHRT, Dnevni Avaz - 07/04/10)
